Zenith CH 650 has a larger cockpit than the 601.
Zenith CH 650 has a larger canopy with more headroom than the 601.
Zenith CH 650 has a swept-back fin and rudder.
Zenith CH 650 engine options include the 120 hp (89 kW) Jabiru 3300.
Zenith CH 650 engine options include the 100 hp (75 kW) Continental O-200.
Zenith CH 650 engine options include the 100 hp (75 kW) Rotax 912ULS.
One hundred Zenith CH 650 aircraft had been completed and flown by December 2011.
Zenith CH 650E is a version for the US light-sport aircraft category.
Zenith CH 650Ei is a version for the European microlight category.

Zenith CH 650Ei has a Rotax 912ULS engine of 100 hp (75 kW).
Zenith CH 650Ei is manufactured as a ready-to-fly aircraft by ICP srl in Italy.
AMD Zodiac XL is the completed US Light Sport Aircraft compliant version of the XL.
AMD Zodiac XLi is the completed US Light Sport Aircraft compliant version of the XL.
AMD Zodiac is produced by Aircraft Manufacturing and Design.
Aircraft Manufacturing and Design is located in Eastman, Georgia, USA.

text:
Zenith CH 650
Modernized version of the 601, with a larger cockpit, a larger canopy with more headroom, swept-back fin and rudder and engine options that include the 120 hp (89 kW) Jabiru 3300, 100 hp (75 kW) Continental O-200 and 100 hp (75 kW) Rotax 912ULS. One hundred had been completed and flown by December 2011.
Zenith CH 650E
Version for the US light-sport aircraft category.
Zenith CH 650Ei
Version for the European microlight category, with a gross weight of 472.5 kg (1,042 lb) and a Rotax 912ULS engine of 100 hp (75 kW). Manufactured as a ready-to-fly aircraft by ICP srl in Italy.
AMD Zodiac XL & XLi
The completed US Light Sport Aircraft compliant version of the XL is the AMD Zodiac produced by Aircraft Manufacturing and Design of Eastman, Georgia, USA.
